==English==

===Etymology===
From "[[dog food]]", jargon for goods sold to customers of a company.

===Verb===
'''[[to]] [[eat]] [[one’s]] [[own]] [[dog]] [[food]]'''
# To test the beta programs that are in the test phase on one's own computers; to [[dogfood]].
# To use or consume the economic [[good]]s or [[service]]s that oneself is producing; to be part of a [[w:closed household economy|closed household economy]]

